  <subsection>
    <title>Coordinate vectors are different in different bases</title>
    <p>
      Suppose that <m>\basis{B} = \left\{ \ve{b}_1, \ve{b}_2 \right\}</m> and
      <m>\basis{C} = \left\{ \ve{c}_1, \ve{c}_2 \right\}</m> are two different bases for <m>\mathbb{R}^2</m>,
      shown below:
    </p>
